    "assignee": null,
    "body": "Sometimes a server needs to preform some asnyc operation before it can respond to a ping request.  To handle this case, we allow the return value of before ping to be a thenable, and then wait on that promise.\r\n\r\nBy returning a thenable instead of sending callback, we easily maintain backwards compatibility. ",
    "closed_at": "2015-10-04T20:13:40Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "body": "The idea is good, but let's not use promises. NMP is entirely callback-based, it'd be weird to have promises in some places. Instead of doing this, we could detect if beforePing.length === 3, in which case we handle the result asynchronously.\r\n\r\n```\r\nfunction cb(err, res) {\r\n  if (err) // ?\r\n  client.write('server_info', { response: JSON.stringify(res) });\r\n}\r\nif (beforePing && beforePing.length === 2)\r\n  cb(null, beforePing(response, client));\r\nelse if (beforePing)\r\n  beforePing(response, client, cb);\r\n```",
            "created_at": "2015-09-30T10:09:40Z",
